Package com.rb.nonbiz.collections

Class HasInstrumentIdPartition<T extends HasInstrumentId>

java.lang.Object
com.rb.nonbiz.collections.HasInstrumentIdPartition<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
PrintsInstruments
public class HasInstrumentIdPartition<T extends HasInstrumentId>
extends java.lang.Object
implements PrintsInstruments
Use this whenever you want to represent having N items with proportions that sum to 1, where the items all have a positive weight.

Partition<T> is used all over the place. This is a specialized class similar to Partition<T>. It was added in Sep 2018, after 300k lines of code were written, so it doesn't appear very frequently. It is particularly useful in situations where there are a lot of instrument IDs as keys (e.g. a stock index membership).

See Also:
Partition, HasInstrumentIdMap
